name: Bin Fan
message:
Fix IndexOutOfBoundsException on async cache

### What changes are proposed in this pull request?

Fix https://github.com/Alluxio/alluxio/issues/13828 and fix
https://github.com/Alluxio/alluxio/issues/13050

This patch will fix a miscaculation of block to async cache

In earlier Alluxio versions prior to
https://github.com/Alluxio/alluxio/pull/13064, users may see the
following errors:
```
2021-03-12 08:36:48,521 ERROR AlluxioFuseFileSystem - Failed to read
file=/data/0.5G_9.txt, offset=536862720, size=8192
java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException: Index: 4, Size: 4
```

After 13064, we will not see the error anymore but caching the last
block when fileSize happens on block size boundary will fail silently.

### Why are the changes needed?

Correct a bug when calculating the block id to async cache, when current
pos is fileSize which is a multiple of blockSize

### Does this PR introduce any user facing changes?

No

name: Zhan Yuan
message:
Add CacheContext to URIStatus to enable per-read metrics

Add functions to URIStatus to track bytes read from cache and external
file system in a per-read basis.
The default implementation does nothing. It is up to the subclass to
decide how to track them.
Presto will use this information to compute query level metrics.
See https://github.com/prestodb/presto/issues/16237 for details.

There are no user facing changes in this commit.

name: Joel Costigliola
message:
Deprecate Java 6/Android assertions entry point. Fixes #1474.

The goal of these entry points was to provide Java6/Android compatible assertions but since we have moved to Java 8 it became more complicated, filtering out java 8 types is not sufficient as we have refactored some assertions implementation to use lambdas and streams that made them improper to use in Java 6. Reverting all this work is not worth it as Android is moving to have more java 8 support.

name: Steven van Beelen
message:
Adjust SnapshotFilter API

Change the SnapshotFilter API to be more to the point. In doing so,
rename `filter` to `allow`, as the function should allow or reject
snapshot data. On top, only the `and` operation is used, which logically
 should be `combine`, as you'd combine these allow methods, not "and"
 them.
